JOHANNESBURG - The state capture commission said that President Cyril Ramaphosa would no longer testify on Monday and Tuesday as previously announced. He was expected to appear on his role as deputy president and president of the country. In a brief notice, commission spokesperson, Reverend Mbuyiselo Stemela, did not say when Ramaphosa would testify. But Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo said that he was concluding oral evidence next week. Zondo has until the end of the month but he wanted more time to write his report. Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.